    {
      "id": "xvXZ",
      "code_hash": "1aea25c0e894128049dd20fbf975c4e8",
      "outputs": [
        {
          "type": "data",
          "data": {
            "text/markdown": "<span class=\"markdown prose dark:prose-invert contents\"><hr />\n<h3 id=\"exercise-implementing-rnn-training\">\u270f\ufe0f\u270f\ufe0f Exercise: Implementing RNN Training \u270f\ufe0f\u270f\ufe0f</h3>\n<hr />\n<span class=\"paragraph\">Your task is to implement the training loop:</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">The training loop will carry out 'truncated backpropagation through time'.</span>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">For each batch, the loop should do the following:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Set the model hidden state to 'None'</li>\n<li>Initiate a for-loop that processes the batch sequentially, in segments of length 'tbptt_step', i.e each segment of the batch should be of shape [N, tbptt_step, 1]</li>\n<li>\n<span class=\"paragraph\">For each segment:</span>\n<ol>\n<li>Zero the gradients in the optimiser</li>\n<li>Get the model predictions for that segment</li>\n<li>Calculate the loss</li>\n<li>Do the backward pass</li>\n<li>call <code>optimiser.step()</code></li>\n<li>Deatch the hidden state, using <code>model.detach_hidden()</code></li>\n<li>append the loss to the loss_list</li>\n</ol>\n</li>\n</ol></span>"
          }
        }
      ],
      "console": []
    },
